name: bones_data
title: 34 Indicators of Skeletal Age From 13 Boys of 6 Months to 18 Years of Chronological Age.
description:
34 indicators of skeletal age (SA) for 13 boys aged 6 months to 18 years. Each indicator is
          categorised with respect to its degree of maturity. 19 are binary 
          (0 immature, 1 mature), 8 are ternary, 1 has 4 grades and 6 have 5
          grades of maturity. For binary items, there is a single threshold
          for the Chronological Age where 50% of individuals are mature for that parameter. Ternary
          items have 2 threshold parameters: first corresponding to the
          CA where 50% of individuals are partially or fully mature, second where 50% are fully mature.,
